{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents certain plastid RNA polymerase sigma factors, including SigB, SigC, SigD and sigF [[cite:PUB00042712], [cite:PUB00042713]]. Development of plastids into chloroplasts is triggered by light. The coordination of light-induced plastid gene expression is directed by both nuclear and plastid genomes. Plastid DNA is transcribed by at least two types of RNA polymerase, plastid-encoded RNA polymerase (PEP) and nuclear-encoded RNA polymerase (NEP). Sigma factors are initiation factors that promote the attachment of RNA polymerase to specific initiation sites and are then released. Sigma factor SigB appears to play a critical role in the coordination of the two genomes for chloroplast development [[cite:PUB00042714]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF000767" "RNA polymerase sigma factor, plastid SigB/SigC/SigD types"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "RNA polymerase sigma factor, SigB/C/D/F, plastid", "short" "RNA_pol_sigma_SigB/C/D/F"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 214, "taxa" 870, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1018, "sets" 0, "proteins" 981, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 656}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR016262", :literature {"PUB00042712" {"URL" nil, "issue" "8", "authors" ["Kanamaru K" "Fujiwara M" "Seki M" "Katagiri T" "Nakamura M" "Mochizuki N" "Nagatani A" "Shinozaki K" "Tanaka K" "Takahashi H."], "ISO_journal" "Plant Cell Physiol.", "DOI_URL" "http://pcp.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/40/8/832", "medline_journal" "Plant Cell Physiol", "title" "Plastidic RNA polymerase sigma factors in Arabidopsis.", "year" 1999, "raw_pages" "832-42", "volume" "40", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 10555304}, "PUB00042713" {"URL" 